<sub>0</sub> is the Dirac delta function centred at 0. The parameter <italic>J</italic> stands for the junction tree representing the graph and |<italic>J</italic>| is the number of edges in the graph represented by the junction tree. <italic>Œæ<sub>J</sub></italic> is a perfect elimination ordering of the nodes in the graph. Both <inline-formula><mml:math id="M35"><mml:msubsup><mml:mi>S</mml:mi><mml:mi>q</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>J</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:msubsup></mml:math></inline-formula> and <inline-formula><mml:math id="M36"><mml:msubsup><mml:mi>H</mml:mi><mml:mi>q</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>J</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:msubsup></mml:math></inline-formula> depend on the graph and are defined in <xref ref-type="sec" rid="S5">Section 2.3</xref>. The index <italic>q</italic>(<italic>k</italic>) is the index of the prime residual <inline-formula><mml:math id="M37"><mml:msubsup><mml:mi>R</mml:mi><mml:mi>q</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>J</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:msubsup></mml:math></inline-formula> that node <italic>k</italic> belongs to in the current node ordering for graph <italic>J</italic>.</p>
      <p id="P29">Finally, the parameters <italic>a<sub>o</sub></italic>, <italic>b<sub>o</sub></italic>, <italic>a<sub>œÄ</sub></italic>, <italic>b<sub>œÄ</sub></italic>, <italic>a<sub>w</sub></italic>, <italic>b<sub>w</sub></italic>, <italic>a<sub>œÑ</sub></italic>, <italic>b<sub>œÑ</sub></italic> and <italic>a<sub>Œ∑</sub></italic>, <italic>b<sub>Œ∑</sub></italic> are fixed. The degrees of freedom <italic>ŒΩ</italic> &gt; <italic>s</italic> ‚àí 1 in the inverse-Wishart distribution is also fixed.</p>
